Position Description
KCP Regional External Contract Manufacturing Supply Chain Leader, APAC

Position Summary
The role is responsible for driving regional end to end supply chain optimization and the effective management of regionally based ECM suppliers, in support of regional and global business needs.
This position is accountable for the delivery of regional supply chain performance objectives: service,   agility, total delivered cost, working capital, growth and innovation; and ensuring that suppliers meet expectations in compliance (social, regulatory and quality), cost savings, supplier OTIF and capacity.

Customers and collaborative partners
Regional and global end users of KCP products, commercial teams (product management, innovation/renovation teams), cross-functional and global supply chain teams (quality, ECM, regulatory, procurement,planning and logistics).

Scope
 All ECM Product Categories, focus on Scientific PPE (apparel, masks, gloves) and skincare
 Annual Spend for suppliers in region: ~$200MM
 Regulatory environment: UL, CE, FDA

Accountabilities

  Ensure compliance: collaborate with respective functions to achieve objectives in regulatory, social, quality, and financial compliance
  Deliver top tier customer service: achieve and sustain customer Tier 1 Customer OTIF &gt; 85%
  Ensure supply: proactively assess risks, capacity and capability within the Global supply network to ensure sufficiency supply vs. the regional and global business plans
  Improve &amp; control costs: achieve 3-5% annual cost improvement across the end-to-end supply chain
  Improve &amp; control working &amp; physical capital: sustain accurate accounting of KC-owned assets at 3rd parties; optimize working capital through supplier reliability initiatives
  Adhere to K-C External Manufacturing Playbook: build regional capability and ensure the utilization of KCP External Manufacturing Practices

Responsibilities
 Develop a comprehensive sourcing &amp; collaboration framework for Scientific PPE and skincare suppliers within the APAC region in alignment with the global team
 Provide leadership and coordination for complex manufacturing/supply chain challenges, commercialization and innovation activities and strategic projects
 Collaborate with the Social Responsibility, Quality and Regulatory teams to develop and execute annual supplier audit plans and drive timely &amp; effective corrective actions with suppliers
 Lead the regional cross-functional process to identify and execute value delivery initiatives
 Drive focused improvements in end to end supply performance leveraging lean concepts
 Build capability and ensure adherence to the K-C External Manufacturing playbook
 Engage strategic suppliers to identify and implement manufacturing and cost improvement programs
 Ensure effective management system to monitor and deliver suppliers performance expectations
 Collaborate with R&amp;E to identify Design for Value and Design for Reliability opportunities within products, packages, and processes
 Lead supplier risk management activities and the execution of category sourcing strategies jointly with the Global Procurement team
 Collaborate with Global Supply Planning to proactively identify capacity requirements over the strategic horizon and develop plans that deliver cost, capacity, working capital and service objectives
 Build regional functional and technical capabilities to preserve the know-how for the ECM categories

Qualifications
 Bachelor's degree in Engineering, Operations Management, Supply Chain or related discipline
 10+ years combined experience within supply chain operational functions, including expert knowledge of and experience in strategic sourcing of finished goods and executing complex supply projects (driving and executing changes in supply base, executing RFPs etc.)
 At least 5 years of experience in leading diverse teams
 Deep expertise in the Scientific PPE supply base across Asia
 Effective and influential communication (verbal and written) in the English language
 Willingness to flex work hours as necessary to engage with global teams and supply partners
 Consistent track record of delivering results while creating a constructive work environment
 Strong interpersonal skills, able to motivate a team, influence members and leaders of other teams, and comfortable communicating upwards to a senior management level
 Ability and experience driving collaboration across business and supply chain functions
 Willingness to challenge the status quo and facilitate different perspectives to drive solution
 Capable of traveling regionally up to 40%

Differentiating Qualifications
 Direct experience in third party sourcing of Scientific apparels, gloves or masks
 Experience managing supply chains or operations in regulated industries
 Fluency in Mandarin Chinese